{","    Reduce { state, action in","      \/\/ Core logic for parent feature","    }","    .ifLet(\\.child, action: \\.child) {","      Child()","    }","  }","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ifLet"},{"type":"text","text":" operator does a number of things to try to enforce correctness:"}]},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"It forces a specific order of operations for the child and parent features. It runs the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"child first, and then the parent. If the order was reversed, then it would be possible for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the parent feature to ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" out the child state, in which case the child feature would not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be able to react to that action. That can cause subtle bugs.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It automatically cancels all child effects when it detects the child’s state is ","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’d","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"out.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automatically "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s out child state when an action is sent for alerts and confirmation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"dialogs."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Reducer\/ifLet(_:action:destination:fileID:filePath:line:column:)-4ub6q"},{"type":"text","text":" for a more advanced operator suited"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to navigation."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/Reducer\/ifLe